# Data Mining Assignment 3

## Human Activity Recognition using Temporal Feature Engineering and ROCKET

This repository contains the final solution for NYCU Data Mining Assignment 3.

The task is Human Activity Recognition (HAR) using wrist accelerometer time-series data.

The final implementation performs:

- strict sequence-level classification
- temporal feature engineering
- ROCKET-style random convolution features
- balanced Ridge classification
- Kaggle submission generation
- automatic analysis and report figure generation

The final pipeline generates exactly one submission file:

```text
submission_final.csv
```

using the format:

```text
Id,Label
```

The best observed public Kaggle score during experimentation was:

```text
0.7752
```

---

# Repository Structure

```text
.
├── solution.py
├── analysis.py
├── submission_final.csv
├── sample_submission.csv
